@graph.rdfs:comment: Authorizataion Control Level for resouces associated with a given resource-group.  Individual authorization control level indicates that access control is available per resource, i.e., authorization can be granted/not-granted on a per resource basis for the resources. Group authorization control level indicates that the authorization is available on group level only, i.e., authorization will be granted/not-granted for all the resources associated with the given resource group. ENUM: [GROUP, INDIVIDUAL]. Default value is set to GROUP. This field is applicable only for non-open data, i.e., when the accessPolicy field is set to value other than OPEN.
@graph.rdfs:label: authControlLevel
